comment: So this has been stuck at 1.030 for some time. I think I have reached the end of attenuation ability with Saison I.  I pitched nottingham yeast 1 week ago, with good resumption of fermentation.  Alas, this won't be ready for the event it was brewed to compete. Ah well.  Maple syrup is apparently not too easy to break down.
After a week with Nottingham chugging along - still 1.028.  I should stop checking....
